<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-21T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-21T13:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">352.1115/4002: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in
                            France</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-21T14:00:00-04:00">August 21, 1937—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>B–290. Your 338, August 20, 4 p.m. The Under Secretary invited De los
                            Rios to call this morning and set forth in some detail our concern over
                            the situation you reported in Gijon. The latter is promptly telegraphing
                            Valencia with a view to straightening the matter out. You may wish to
                            supplement this by further communication with Thurston in order that the
                            latter may inform you as soon as new and specific orders have been sent
                            to Governor at Gijon.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>